56	2026-05-12-z	2026-05-12	Feature	Three small but high-impact polish changes to the Content Calendar so the day-to-day editing flow stays focused on upcoming work and the in-place caption editor reaches feature parity with the modal: (a) past days are now hidden by default — the calendar opens straight onto today + upcoming so the user always sees the next thing to ship instead of scrolling past archived rows; (b) the inline `<Editable>` Caption field in the post-detail panel now has the same `Bold selection` action that already exists on the Edit / Generate modal caption (Unicode bold that survives Facebook & Instagram paste); (c) the modal caption textarea is now a uniform 2 rows for both brands instead of 5 rows on Virtu / 2 on GHS, so the editor stays compact and the form fits on a laptop screen without scrolling.	["Past-day rows in `CalendarGrid` (`pages/content-calendar.tsx`) now return `null` whenever `past && !showPast`, instead of rendering the previous thin one-line collapsed row. This means the visible day list starts at today and runs forward — past content is fully out of the way unless the user explicitly clicks the existing toolbar `View past` toggle, which still expands every past day in the month back to its full row exactly as before. No data is ever filtered out server-side; this is a purely UI presentation toggle, so all past posts remain queryable, exportable to PDF, and reachable from share links and the Skipped Posts page. Removed the now-unreachable thin-row JSX block (~40 lines) so the grid renderer has only one rendering path and is easier to reason about.", "Extended the inline `Editable` field component with a new optional `withBoldButton?: boolean` prop. When set on a `kind=\\"textarea\\"` field, the label header gains a right-aligned `Bold selection` button (with the existing `Bold` lucide icon) that, while editing, calls the existing `applyBoldToTextarea` helper against the field's own `textareaRef` — the same Unicode-bold transform (`isBoldUnicode` / `toBoldUnicode` / `fromBoldUnicode`) used by the Edit / Generate modal caption, so a selection that is already bold gets toggled back to plain. `onMouseDown={e => e.preventDefault()}` keeps the textarea focused so the selection survives the click and the cursor doesn't blur-commit prematurely. Wired this prop on the post-detail panel's `<Editable label=\\"Caption\\">` so the same affordance is available in the inline editor that was previously modal-only — the affordance is hidden on every other Editable instance (visual direction, resources, etc.) since they don't carry social-media copy.", "Modal caption textarea (`NewPostForm` / Edit-post body) reduced from `rows={isVirtu ? 5 : 2}` to a flat `rows={2}` for both Virtu Ferries and Gozo Highspeed. Previously Virtu had a 5-row caption box dating from when the modal also held the AI-suggestion preview inside it; the suggestion preview now lives outside, so the extra height was just empty space pushing other fields below the fold. Going to 2 rows matches the GHS sizing the user already preferred and the textarea still grows as the user types because the parent `inputCls` keeps `resize-none` only on overflow — content is never clipped, just no longer takes 3 extra rows of vertical space when empty. No schema, route, or data changes."]	2026-05-14 21:24:18.576613+00	1
57	2026-05-12-aa	2026-05-12	Strategy	Replaced the Virtu Ferries content pillar system across every surface — definitions, AI agent prompt, monthly planning targets, the pillars DB table, and every existing content_posts row — with the newly approved 7-pillar set: Choose Virtu, Choose Sicily (Maltese-facing), Choose Malta (Italy-facing), Virtu Recommends, The Crossing, The Community, and Flexible / Operational. Retired the old names (Why VF, Why Sicily, Why Malta, VF Experience, VF Recommends, For the Feed, Sicily/Malta Experience, VF Recommends Malta) so every content card, dropdown, and prompt now uses the same vocabulary the brand actually uses. Layout, styling, anchor-day cadence, and the 25-posts-per-month framework are preserved verbatim — only naming, definitions, and pillar references changed.	["Updated `lib/brand-knowledge/src/index.ts` in three places so the React UI and the agent prompt builder both pick up the new pillars without further sync: (a) `socialMedia.pillars` (5 pillars + Flexible/Operational with the role + definition copy from the approved spec); (b) `monthlyPlanning.pillarsEnglish` with 'Choose Sicily' for the Maltese-facing channels; (c) `monthlyPlanning.pillarsItalian` with 'Choose Malta' for the Italy-facing channel and Italian translations of every definition. The shared `formatBrandKnowledgeAsPrompt(slug)` helper consumes these arrays so the agent's system prompt automatically reflects the new pillars on the next request — no second source to update. Frontend pages (`/social-media`, `/monthly-planning`) re-render via `useBrandContent` with no schema changes (`PillarOverview` already supports the longer titles).", "Rewrote `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/brandGuidelines.ts` CONTENT PILLARS section in full: added a market-rule preamble explaining the Choose Sicily / Choose Malta split (Facebook Malta + Instagram = Choose Sicily, Facebook Italy = Choose Malta), then replaced the five-pillar definitions with six (Choose Virtu, Choose Sicily/Choose Malta, Virtu Recommends, The Crossing, The Community, Flexible / Operational), each with role + goal + what-it-includes + tone + rule + anchor day. Explicit 'Do NOT create an Offers pillar' note — offers now sit under Choose Virtu, Virtu Recommends, or Flexible / Operational. MONTHLY FRAMEWORK pillar targets and anchor-day grid rewritten to match (Mon=Choose Virtu, Fri=The Community, Sun=The Crossing, Sat=Virtu Recommends + Flexible/Operational schedule, Tue/Wed/Thu = Choose Sicily/Malta rotation). CONTENT GENERATION RULES line 6 ('Link in bio to book') and HARD RULES line 5 ('Never include a booking CTA in a For the Feed post') updated to reference 'Choose Virtu' and 'Community'. API server restarted so the live system prompt reflects the new pillars immediately.", "Updated `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/content.ts` so the AI monthly-plan generator emits the new pillar names: (a) `DEFAULT_PILLARS` rewritten to the 7-pillar list (Choose Virtu/both, Choose Sicily/english, Choose Malta/italian, Virtu Recommends/both, The Crossing/both, The Community/both, Flexible / Operational/both — used by the `/api/content/pillars` GET fallback when the table is empty); (b) the English-market and Italian-market pillar blocks inside `buildMonthlyPlanPrompt` rewritten with the new names + one-line definitions; (c) the Saturday weekly-schedule HARD RULE flipped from `pillar: \\"Why VF\\"` to `pillar: \\"Flexible / Operational\\"` (per the spec rule that Flexible / Operational is reserved for required schedules and service info, never editorial); (d) the PILLAR TARGETS section under POSTING STRUCTURE rewritten to the new mapping (Choose Virtu = 3 offer posts, Choose Sicily/Malta ≈ 9, Virtu Recommends ≈ 5, The Crossing ≈ 4, The Community ≈ 3, Flexible / Operational reserved for the Saturday schedule + disruption only). The 25-posts-per-month total, format targets, and pinned-idea rules are unchanged.", "Migrated the live database in a single transaction: TRUNCATEd `pillars` for 