58	2026-05-15-a	2026-05-15	Feature	Added a live Sicily events feed to the Virtu Ferries hub, mirroring the existing Gozo Highspeed → eventsingozo.com feed but for the destination side of the Malta ↔ Pozzallo route. The Events page now ends with a read-only `visitsicily.info` section showing every event scraped hourly from the official Visit Sicily portal — title, date range, location, description, categories, plus a direct link to the source page and (where listed) the official event website. The feed is brand-gated to Virtu Ferries only and is also injected into the Brand Agent's system prompt as a `# SICILY LIVE EVENTS` block, so the agent can reference real, current Sicilian events when proposing 'Choose Sicily' or 'Virtu Recommends' content without inventing them.	["Built a server-side scraper at `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/sicilyEvents.ts` that walks 5 RSS pages of `visitsicily.info/en/category/categorie-en/evento-en/feed/` in parallel (~50 events), dedupes by URL, then fetches each event's detail page with bounded concurrency 6 and a 12s per-request timeout. The detail-page parser flattens the HTML and locates the structured footer block visitsicily emits (`LOCATION / START dd/mm/yyyy hh:mm / END / WEBSITE / E-MAIL / SOCIAL / PLACES / CATEGORIES / AROUND`) by walking labels in order, so each event yields typed `start`, `end`, `location`, `website`, `social`, and `categories[]`. The body description is sliced from the universal Avada-theme `Detail … Share this content!` markers and capped at 1200 chars to protect the agent prompt budget. Image is taken from `og:image`. Exposed `GET /api/sicily-events` (returns `{source, fetchedAt, cached, count, events[]}`) and `getSicilyEvents(force?)` for in-process consumers; results are cached for 1h with an inflight-promise guard so the first request after expiry doesn't fan out concurrent crawls. Route is brand-gated — non-virtu-ferries brands get a 404 — and supports `?refresh=1` to bust the cache. Registered the router in `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/index.ts`.", "Added a `SicilyEventsSection` component to `artifacts/virtu-ferries-brand-hub/src/pages/events.tsx` that renders below the existing manual events list, gated to `activeBrand.slug === 'virtu-ferries'` (the Gozo feed stays gated to GHS — both can never be visible at once). UI mirrors the Gozo feed's hub-chrome light theme: a `Live feed` eyebrow, the `visitsicily.info` heading, an attribution + photo-rights paragraph, last-fetched timestamp, and a `Refresh` button that POSTs to `/api/sicily-events?refresh=1`. Each event renders as a `SicilyFeedCard` with the brand-blue accent stripe, mini date stamp, formatted en-GB date range, MapPin location, expandable description with Read more / Show less, and lucide `Globe`/`ExternalLink` actions linking to the official event website and the visitsicily source page respectively. Events are grouped into month rails via `groupSicilyByMonth` reusing the existing `MonthRail` primitive, and 'Date TBA' entries fall to the bottom. The new component uses the same `useState`/`useCallback`/`useEffect` plumbing already imported in events.tsx — no new dependencies.", "Wired the same feed into the Brand Agent's system prompt at `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/chat.ts`. `buildKnowledgeContext` now takes `brandSlug` alongside `brandId`; when the active brand is `virtu-ferries`, after the existing `# UPCOMING EVENTS (from the events database)` block, the builder calls `getSicilyEvents()` (which hits the same 1h cache the route uses, so this adds zero latency on hot turns), filters to the next 25 events whose start date is today or later, and emits a `# SICILY LIVE EVENTS (from visitsicily.info, refreshed hourly)` block listing each as `[YYYY-MM-DD → end] Title · Place [Cat1, Cat2] — sourceUrl`. The block carries explicit usage guidance in its preamble — credit visitsicily.info, treat their photos as visual reference only — so the agent reproduces the same attribution discipline the UI shows