60	2026-05-15-c	2026-05-15	Bugfix	Fixed a Content Calendar bug where Saturday weekly-schedule posts (and any other 'English Market' rows) were visible in the calendar list view but missing from the new-post date picker's mini-calendar dots. Root cause was a legacy market label — the old `English Market` value was renamed to `Maltese Market` across the hub a while ago, but production rows seeded from older snapshots still carried the legacy value. The new-post mini calendar filters posts by strict equality `p.market === form.market`, and since the dropdown only emits `Maltese Market` / `Italian Market`, every legacy `English Market` row silently dropped out — including the auto-generated Saturday `Weekly Schedule` posts on `Flexible / Operational`.	["Added `MARKET_RENAME_MAP` ({ 'English Market' → 'Maltese Market', 'English' → 'Maltese Market' }) and a paired `rewriteLegacyMarkets(client)` function in `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/bootstrapFromSnapshot.ts`, mirroring the existing `rewriteLegacyPillars` pattern. Wired it into the same `sp_legacy_rewrites` SAVEPOINT block at the end of `bootstrapFromSnapshot`, so on every production startup it runs `UPDATE content_posts SET market = 'Maltese Market' WHERE market IN ('English Market','English')`. Idempotent — once normalised, the next startup updates 0 rows and self-disables. The error label was widened from 'Legacy pillar rewrite failed' to 'Legacy pillar/market rewrite failed' so failures stay observable. Dev is unaffected because the bootstrap is gated on `NODE_ENV === 'production'` and the dev DB already only holds the canonical `Maltese Market` / `Italian Market` values.", "Verified via the production-DB read query that the bug surface was real before the fix: brand_id=1 had 43 rows with `market = 'English Market'` and 1 stray `market = 'English'`, including the Saturday weekly-schedule posts on 06.06, 13.06, 20.06, and 27.06. brand_id=2 had 62 such rows. After republish, all 105+ rows will be normalised to `Maltese Market` and the mini-picker dots will line up with the list view. No frontend changes needed — the calendar already renders dots for every `Maltese Market` row."]	2026-05-15 09:43:23.826268+00	1
61	2026-05-15-d	2026-05-15	UX	Removed the secondary 'Edit post' workflow from the Content Calendar's post detail modal. Every field in the modal — title, platform, pillar, format, date, time, assignee, caption, visual direction, visual reference URL, link, and Drive folder — is now always-on inline-editable: no pencil button, no toggle into edit mode, no separate Edit Post Modal trip. Click any field, type, blur (or press Enter / ⌘+Enter for the caption), and the change PATCHes immediately with the same loading + green-check confirmation indicator next to each label.	["Refactored the shared `Editable` component in `artifacts/virtu-ferries-brand-hub/src/pages/content-calendar.tsx` to drop its `editing` state for the `text`, `url`, and `textarea` kinds. Inputs and textareas are now rendered live in every render with a quiet `border-[#E4E4E7] hover:border-[#A1A1AA]` resting style and the existing `focus:border-[#1e82b4]/60 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1e82b4]/30` focus state, so the affordance is the field itself rather than a 'click to edit' button. Save fires on blur (or Enter for single-line, ⌘/Ctrl+Enter for textarea); Escape reverts to the last saved value and blurs. Removed the now-redundant Save / Cancel button row from the textarea variant — the `commit()` flow already debounces by comparing trimmed-to-null against the previous value, and the per-label saving / saved indicator stays put. The `select`, `date`, and `time` kinds were already always-live, so they were left untouched. The `linkify` and `displayClassName` props remain in the signature for backwards-compat but `linkify` now renders auto-linked URLs as a small caption underneath the textarea instead of as the (previously click-to-open) display surface.", "Replaced the title block at the top of `CardDetailModal` with the same always-on pattern: a single `<input>` with the bold heading typography, transparent border at rest, hover-revealed `border-[#E4E4E7]` rule, and the existing brand-blue focus border. Saves on blur via the existing `saveTitle` helper (Enter blurs, Escape reverts). Dropped the `editingTitle` / `setEditingTitle` state, the `startEditTitle` helper, and the secondary pencil icon button — all dead code now that nothing toggles the field in or out of edit mode.", "Removed the 'Edit post' button from the modal footer and dropped the `onEdit` prop from `CardDetailModal`'s signature. The parent at line 3854 no longer passes `onEdit` either, so the legacy code path that closed the detail modal and re-opened the heavier `EditPostModal` is gone end-to-end. Duplicate, Download brief, and Delete remain in the footer because they're not field edits — they're post-level actions. The orphaned `Pencil` lucide import was removed; `EditPostModal` itself is left in place because the same code is still used by other entry points (the new-post flow). Verified by typecheck — only pre-existing unrelated errors remain."]	2026-05-15 10:06:12.390589+00	1
62	2026-05-15-e	2026-05-15	UX	Four targeted upgrades to the Content Calendar's post detail modal: (1) the date picker icon is now visible on the new light theme, (2) two new formats — 'UGC' and '4 Photos' — are selectable on every post, (3) a brand-new always-on inline-editable 'Graphic Text' textarea sits directly under Visual Direction so on-image / overlay copy lives next to the visual brief instead of being buried in the caption or notes, and (4) the underlying database schema gained a nullable `graphic_text` column on `content_posts` so the new field round-trips through GET, PATCH, POST, and the production data snapshot without any extra plumbing.	["Added a nullable `graphic_text: text('graphic_text')` column to `lib/db/src/schema/contentPosts.ts` and pushed it to the dev database via `pnpm --filter @workspace/db run push`. The column is intentionally nullable (not `.notNull().default('')` like `visual_direction`) so existing rows stay clean — an empty string would force every legacy post to render an empty 'Graphic Text' label, whereas `null` lets the inline-editable component show its placeholder instead. The `Editable.commit()` flow already converts trimmed-empty input back to `null`, so blanking the field clears it cleanly. The production snapshot bootstrap (`bootstrapFromSnapshot.ts`) automatically picks the new column up on the next prebuild dump because it dumps `content_posts` whole-row, so no `TABLES` array edit was needed; the prod DB will gain the column on the next deploy via the same drizzle push that already runs against prod.", "Wired `graphic_text` through the api-server PATCH route in `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/content.ts`: added it to the destructure list and to the conditional update spread as `...(graphic_text !== undefined && { graphic_text: graphic_text || null })`, mirroring the resources / visual_reference_url pattern so an empty string from the UI normalises back to `null` in the DB. Also added `graphic_text?: string` to the POST insert payload type at the top of the file; the existing `...p` insert spread carries it through, and the GET /content/posts list route uses `.select()` (whole row) so it auto-flows back to the client with no extra change. Verified the two narrow `.select({...})` projections at lines 346 (post history) and 1535 (plan generator) deliberately do not include `graphic_text` because neither surface displays it.", "On the frontend (`artifacts/virtu-ferries-brand-hub/src/pages/content-calendar.tsx`): added `graphic_text: string | null` to the local `ContentPost` type so TypeScript propagates the new field through every consumer, then dropped a new `<Editable label='Graphic Text' kind='textarea' value={post.graphic_text ?? null} placeholder='On-image / on-graphic copy (headline, overlay text, CTAs)…' onSave={v => patchPost({ graphic_text: v })} />` directly under the existing Visual Direction Editable inside `CardDetailModal`. It uses the same always-on inline-edit pattern shipped in 2026-05-15-d, so there's no separate save button — blur or Escape commits or reverts, and the per-label saving / saved indicator already in `Editable` works for free. `share-view.tsx` and `nico.tsx` were intentionally left alone: the public share page deliberately sanitises field-level data and the nico page uses a narrower projection — neither displays graphic text today.", "Extended the `FORMATS` array in `content-calendar.tsx` from `['Single Image','Carousel','Reel','Video','Story']` to `['Single Image','Carousel','Reel','Video','Story','UGC','4 Photos']`. Both the post detail modal's Format Editable (kind='select', options=FORMATS) and the New Post modal's Format dropdown (also reading FORMATS) pick up the two new options automatically. Existing rows with non-matching format strings keep displaying their stored value because the select renders the raw string above the dropdown — no migration required.", "Fixed the Content Calendar's date picker icon being nearly invisible on the light hub theme: replaced `[color-scheme:dark]` with `[color-scheme:light]` on all four input className strings in `content-calendar.tsx` — the inline-edit date input inside `Editable`, the `inputCls` shared by `NewPostModal`, the `compactInput` used by the in-modal date / time pickers, and the small checkbox helper. `color-scheme:dark` was telling the browser to render the native picker chrome (calendar icon, clear button, dropdown chevron) in dark mode — black icons on a now-white field — making them effectively unreadable. With `color-scheme:light` the browser paints the native picker UI in the light variant that matches the rest of the form. No JS or layout change needed; this is a CSS-only fix."]	2026-05-15 10:15:53.965261+00	1
